info.description:
# DataRobot AI API Client

## Installation

```bash
$ pip install datarobot-ai
```

Python versions 2.7, 3.5, and 3.6 are supported. Other versions may work but are not tested.

## Getting Started

The first step in working with the client is creating a new instance of it. But first you need your
API Key from [developers.datarobot.com](https://developers.datarobot.com). Once you have a key, you can
create a new `DataRobotAIClient` using that key.

```python
from datarobotai.client import DataRobotAIClient
ai = DataRobotAIClient(key='fill-in-key-here')

# you can print client to get info about it
print(ai)
# will print the following:
# DataRobotAIClient version 1.0.xx connecting to 'https://developers.datarobot.com/aiapi' with key 'fill-in-key-here'
```

For a more complete example of using this client, see our [quickstart](https://developers.datarobot.com/learn/getting-started/quickstart/)
